io.github.pr0methean.betterrandom.util.spliterator

Class AbstractSupplierSpliterator<TSupplier,TConsumer,TSplitInto>

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.github.pr0methean.betterrandom.util.spliterator.AbstractSupplierSpliterator<TSupplier,TConsumer,TSplitInto>
  • Type Parameters:
    TSupplier - The type of the supplier of output values. A specification or unboxed-primitive equivalent of Supplier.
    TConsumer - The consumer type that tryAdvance(Object) receives. A specification or unboxed-primitive equivalent of Consumer
    TSplitInto - The return type of trySplit(). Should be a self-reference (i.e. ConcreteSupplierSpliterator extends AbstractSupplierSpliterator<T, U, ConcreteSupplierSpliterator>).
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DoubleSupplierSpliterator, IntSupplierSpliterator, LongSupplierSpliterator

    public abstract class AbstractSupplierSpliterator<TSupplier,TConsumer,TSplitInto>
extends Object
    An unordered, concurrent spliterator (possibly unboxed) that invokes a supplier (possibly unboxed) to get its values. Has a preset size if it isn't the result of a trySplit(), but shares its total size with the other splits if it is.
    Author:
    Chris Hennick

      • AbstractSupplierSpliterator

        protected AbstractSupplierSpliterator(AtomicLong remaining,
                                      AtomicLong splitsRemaining,
                                      TSupplier supplier,
                                      boolean sized)
        Create an instance sharing the given AtomicLongs to track the total remaining size and the remaining number of splits that are to be allowed. Used for splitting.
        Parameters:
        remaining - An AtomicLong (shared between splits) that stores how many more items will be output by tryAdvance(Object).
        splitsRemaining - An AtomicLong (shared between splits) that stores how many more times the trySplit() command will return non-null.
        supplier - The supplier to wrap.
        sized - Should be true if this is the root spliterator, and false otherwise (since the root spliterator stores the total size, and concurrent splits may compete to exhaust it).

      • internalSplit

        protected abstract TSplitInto internalSplit(AtomicLong remaining,
                                            AtomicLong splitsRemaining)
        Splits off a new instance that uses the same Supplier, and shares its counts of remaining items and remaining permitted splits with this one. Doesn't decrement the number of remaining permitted splits (that's done in trySplit()). Should wrap a constructor that ultimately calls AbstractSupplierSpliterator(remaining, splitsRemaining, supplier, false).
        Parameters:
        remaining - An AtomicLong (shared between splits) that stores how many more items will be output by tryAdvance(Object).
        splitsRemaining - An AtomicLong (shared between splits) that stores how many more times the trySplit() command will return non-null.
        Returns:
        a descendant spliterator.

      • estimateSize

        public long estimateSize()
        Returns an upper bound on the number of remaining items.
        Returns:
        the total number of items remaining in the root spliterator, and thus an upper bound on the number available to any one descendant.
        See Also:
        Spliterator.estimateSize()

        public int characteristics()
